[Diff(EQUAL,"/*¶ * The purpose of this exercise is to teach you four different ways of using¶ * OpenMP to parallelize a sequential C++ program for summing the¶ * first N natural numbers.¶ *¶ * The sequential solution is in the file:¶ *¶ * sum_sequential.cpp.¶ *¶ * The solutions you will create will in the files with the term parallel:¶ *¶ * sum_parallel_for_local_var.cpp¶ * sum_parallel_for_reduction.cpp¶ * sum_parallel.cpp¶ * sum_sequential.cpp¶ *¶ * Each of these files is a copy of the sequential solution.¶ * Your task is to modify them to create the four OpenMP solutions.¶ *¶ * Each file defines a procedure or method that can be called from a main¶ * program. This file provides the main function, which calls the sequential¶ * solution and all four parallel solutions.¶ *¶ * The unmodified parallel solutions will have the same output as the sequential¶ * solution. The modified solution will compute the same result but print different¶ * output. This is because the sequential and parallel solutions print not only¶ *¶ */¶¶#include <iostream> // for C++ I/O¶#include <omp.h> // for open mp calls¶¶using namespace std;// for C++ IO¶//need to declare headers of external functions called¶void sum_sequential(double* anArray, int aSize);¶void sum_parallel_for_reduction(double* anArray, int aSize);¶void sum_parallel(double* anArray, int aSize);¶void sum_parallel_for_local_var(double* anArray, int aSize);¶¶const int SIZE = 1000;¶¶/**¶ * Called by each of the summing alternatives¶ */¶void printSumWithTimes (int aSum, int aStart, int anEnd) {¶ cout << "Sum: " << aSum << endl;¶ cout << "Took: " << anEnd - aStart << endl;¶}¶void printNumThreads() {¶ cout << "threads:" << omp_get_num_threads() << endl;¶}¶/**¶ * an array to learn how much concurrency occurred¶ */¶int MAX_THREADS = 100;¶double* threadsLastIndex = new double[MAX_THREADS];¶int numThreads;¶¶¶void recordThreadIndex(int anIndex) {¶ int thread = omp_get_thread_num();¶ if (thread >= MAX_THREADS) {¶ return;¶ }¶ threadsLastIndex[thread] = anIndex;¶ numThreads = omp_get_num_threads();¶}¶void initThreadRecording() {¶ numThreads = 0;¶ for (int i = 0; i < MAX_THREADS; i++) {¶ threadsLastIndex[i] = -1;¶ }¶}¶void initArray (double* anArray, int aSize ) {¶ for(int i = 0; i < aSize; i++) {¶ anArray[i]=i;¶ }¶}¶void initArrayAndTracing (double* anArray, int aSize ) {¶ initArray(anArray, aSize);¶ initThreadRecording();¶}¶¶void printThreadLastIndices() {¶ for (int i = 0; i < numThreads; i++) {¶ cout << "thread:" << i << " lastIndex:" << threadsLastIndex[i] << endl;¶ }¶ cout << "_____________________________" << endl;¶}¶¶¶¶void sum_driver()¶{¶ double* anArray = new double[SIZE];¶ initArray(anArray, SIZE);¶ initThreadRecording();¶ sum_sequential(anArray, SIZE);¶ printThreadLastIndices();¶ initThreadRecording();¶ sum_parallel_for_reduction(anArray, SIZE);¶ printThreadLastIndices();¶ initThreadRecording();¶ sum_parallel_for_local_var(anArray, SIZE);¶ printThreadLastIndices();¶ initThreadRecording();¶ sum_parallel(anArray, SIZE);¶ printThreadLastIndices();¶ initThreadRecording();¶}¶")]

i < MAX_THREADS; i++) {¶ threadsLastIndex[i] = -1;¶ }¶}¶void initArray (double* anArray, int aSize ) {¶ for(int i = 0; i < aSize; i++) {¶ anArray[i]=i;¶ }¶}¶void initArrayAndTracing (double* anArray, int aSize ) {¶ initArray(anArray, aSize);¶ initThreadRecording();¶}¶¶void printThreadLastIndices() {¶ for (int i = 0;
